cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.DC 

This paper discusses the design and development of a software-defined communications ecosystem for wireless networks. It involves the use of algorithms to dynamically control the communications stack, which falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the need for security and reliability in wireless networks, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of algorithms and software-defined networking also involves the use of control systems (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the need for efficient resource allocation, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
